Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut each @Plain Taco Tortillas{6} into 8 triangles (use #scissors if easier).

Place on a large #baking tray in a single layer and drizzle with @oil{}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bake on the top shelf in the oven until lightly golden brown and crisp,
~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. Keep an eye on them to make sure they
> colour evenly.

Heat a large #frying pan on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams}. Fry until the mince has browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a spoon to break it up as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press).

Drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1%carton} in a #sieve.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

Once the mince has browned, add the garlic and @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}
and fry, ~{1%minute}.

Stir through the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp}
and @Water{75%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to a boil, then add the black beans. Lower the heat and simmer until the
mixture has thickened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @Butter{20%g} until melted.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it
looks little thick.

Share the Mexican spiced beef and bean mixture between your serving bowls.

Sprinkle over the cheese and top with a dollop of @Soured Cream{75%g} to finish.

Serve the nachos alongside for dipping. Enjoy!